Financial accounting legislation. Basic principles and concepts of accounting. Organisation of accounting in an enterprise. Main accounting procedures for groups of balance sheet items: current assets, fixed assets, liabilities, equity. Calculation of revenues and expenses, sales, transactions and the economic return. Annual reports.Objectives/eesmärkid:  After completing the course the student will be aware of the objectives and importance of financial accounting, acquire professional terminology, understand how to apply the financial accounting system, and acquire the knowledge to make the right financial decisions based on accounting, both in business and non-governmental organizations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows and understands how to apply legislation regulating financial accounting; 2) knows how to determine the status of assets, liabilities and equity; 3) understands the continuous reporting of economic transactions in order to assess the financial situation of an enterprise; 4) knows how to prepare financial accounting reports and how to use financial statements in making management decisions; 5) knows the differences in the management of financial accounting between NGOs and budgetary state agencies.
